newsitem.title: EGYPT: Egyptian overnight rates little changed.
newsitem.headline: Egyptian overnight rates little changed.

text.p: Overnight interbank rates on the Egyptian pound in the private sector were little changed on Monday at around 10 percent, from a range between 9 1/2 and 10 1/8 percent on Sunday, bankers said. One banker cited 9 1/2.
One-week rates were slightly higher, at between 10 and 10 1/4, from between 9 3/4 and 10 1/16 on Sunday, they added.
A second bank confirmed Sunday's reports that the four big public-sector banks were willing to break a longstanding taboo on lending overnight at below 10 1/2 percent.
